docs.snippet: WARREN, Ohio, July 10 (AP) -- Louise Suggs of Atlanta, finishing two strokes ahead of Patty Berg of Chicago, won the $16,000 Trumbull women's open golf tournament today with a 72-hole total of 288, four strokes under par.

docs.snippet: NEWPORT, R.I, July 11 -- President Elsenhower broadly outlined today his plan to improve living standards and strengthen democracy throughout Latin America. He said Cuba would have to change her ways to participate.
